- `engineering:testing-strategy` — for planning coverage depth per phase beyond what's listed in §12/§13
- `engineering:code-review` — run before merging each phase's PR
- `engineering:debug` — structured debugging if a probe/evaluation/contract interaction misbehaves
- `engineering:deploy-checklist` — use directly for Phase 8
- `engineering:documentation` — for `README.md` / `ARCHITECTURE.md` polish in Phase 9
- `frontend-design` — already referenced in §10; re-consult it if extending the dashboard beyond what `DESIGN-vercel.md` specifies (e.g. the breach timeline, which isn't a Vercel marketing-site pattern)

**Worth checking on the [skills.sh](https://skills.sh) marketplace** (third-party, community-built — verify before installing, see note below): search by category rather than name since rankings/authors change —
- A **Solidity/Hardhat** skill (testing patterns, gas-optimization conventions) for Phase 4
- A **Postgres/Supabase migrations** skill for Phase 1
- A **Playwright E2E** skill for Phase 7/8
- A **smart-contract security checklist** skill to sanity-check `SLAEscrow.sol` before calling it "audited-style" in your README (don't claim a real audit if you only ran a checklist)

> A quick safety note for the marketplace itself: skills can contain code that runs in your environment. Before installing any third-party skill, check both its install count and its author — don't rely on a name alone, and don't install something with a low install count from an unverified author just because the description matches. I haven't verified current rankings or specific skill names on skills.sh myself, so treat the categories above as a search starting point, not a recommendation of a specific package.

