## 16. Deployment Checklist (quick reference, full detail in Phase 8)

- [ ] Supabase production project + migrations applied
- [ ] Render API service live, `/api/healthz` returns 200
- [ ] Render cron jobs scheduled and firing (check logs after first scheduled run)
- [ ] Vercel deployment live, env vars set, builds green
- [ ] Sepolia contract deployed + verified, oracle wallet funded
- [ ] One full demo cycle run successfully against production (not just locally)

## 17. Resume / Interview Talking Points (draft — refine after building)

- "Built an end-to-end SLA monitoring and enforcement platform that detects third-party API uptime/latency breaches and programmatically settles a testnet escrow contract — no human in the breach-to-consequence loop."
- "Designed the downtime-detection policy to require consecutive probe failures before flagging an outage, avoiding false positives from transient network blips — a real reliability-engineering trade-off, not just a CRUD feature."
- "Implemented a minimal, access-controlled Solidity escrow contract (oracle pattern, reentrancy-guarded) with full Hardhat test coverage of the payout and access-control paths."
- "Built the monitoring pipeline (probe → aggregate → evaluate → notify/settle) as decoupled, independently testable stages, deployed as a Render web service plus scheduled cron workers against a Supabase Postgres backend."

